description:
Sarah Brown, Vogue’s former beauty director and a judge on American Beauty Star, spills behind-the-scenes info on the reality competition show, discusses her 15 years at the magazine, and reveals the very best foundation in the world. Before that, we talk about new hair and body products using micellar technology; lasers that rejuvenate your lady parts (drink every time we say “vaginal”); and give a movie review of The Kevyn Aucoin Story: Larger Than Life.

Become a member at https://plus.acast.com/s/fatmascara.
